主要學術著作或得過之獎項


文學院 教學特優教師(2007)
 主要學術著作  1. 期刊論文（Journal Papers）: 
                  2002.   “Encountering  the Cultural Aporia: Multiculturalism as a Global/ Local Cultural Nexus.” Journal  of Contemporary Thought 16.2: 63-84.

                  2002.   “(Un)Packing  the Past: Problems of the Sansei’s Hybrid Identity in Obasan.” Fiction  and Drama 14: 115-134.
                  2003.   “On Violence, Justice and Deconstruction.” Concentric:  Studies in English Literature and Linguistics 29.1: 23-46.
                  2003.   “Re-writing the Subject: The Thrownness of Heideggerian  Being in the Multicultural Condition.” Canadian Review of Comparative  Literature 30.3-4:  495-503 . 

                  2004.   “A  Prosaics of Postcolonial Multiculturalism in The Moor’s Last Sigh.” Fiction and Drama 15: 114-125.
                  2004.   ＜「幽靈」與「朋友」：論解構主義的政治轉向＞。《中外文學》32.8（元月號）: 77-112。 
                  2004.   “A Shadow-behind or a  Light-ahead: Redeeming the Past of Race and Ethnicity in America?” (Reviewing Race and Ethnicity in America: A Concise History. Ed.  Ronald H. Bayor). American Studies 45.2  (Spring): 136-7. 

                  2004.   “Nietzsche’s Forgotten  Umbrella: Memory, Life and History.” EurAmerica 34.2 (June): 203-230. 
                  2005.   “Transgressive Flows: Theorizing a  Hauntology of Anti-Globalization.” Concentric:  Literary and Cultural Studies 31.1 (January): 123-46. 

                  2005.   ＜上帝的禮物：再探「禮物與交換經濟」＞。《中外文學》33.9（貳月號）: 11-41.
                  2005   “On Narrative: Story, History and Truth.” Journal  of Contemporary Thought 19.2 (Summer): 25-42.
                  2005   “Will to Power: A Nietzschean Reading of a Clash of Two Religious  Civilizations.” 《成大宗教與文化學報》5.1 (December): 199-230.

                  2005   ＜德希達的幽靈哲學與政治＞。第二期 （十二月號）：47-90.
                  2006.  ＜暴力經濟學：倫理、法律與正義＞。《文山評論》第六期 (三月號): 1-22.
                  2006.  “Limits and Beyond: Greenblatt, New  Historicism and a Feminist Genealogy.” Intergrams: Studies in Languages and Literatures 7.1: 1-29.

                  2006.  ＜友誼政治與父權治理＞。《當代中國哲學學報》1.4（六月號）: 33-54. 
                  2006.   “The Face of the Past:  Memory and Forgetting in The Bonesetter’s Daughter.” Fiction and  Drama 17 (December): 1-20.

                  2007.  ＜論傅柯的《規訓與懲罰》＞《文化研究@嶺南》第三期 (一月份). http://www.ln.edu.hk/mcsln/3rd_issue/
                  2007.  “‘The Time is Out of Joint’:  A Derridean Reading of Virginia Woolf’s Mrs. Dalloway” (co-author with Fay Chen) EurAmerica 37.2(June). 
                    2. 會議論文（Conference Papers）:
                  1999. 02.  “Greenblatt, New  Historicism and Beyond.” MBBAS Conference. U.K.:  University of Warwick.
                  1999. 05.  “The Hauntology of Histories in Salman  Rushdie’s Midnight’s Children.” International Conference on  Refiguring History: Between the Psyche and the Polis. U.K.: University   of Newcastle.

                  2001. 05.  “Re-writing the Subject: The Thrownness of  Being in the Multicultural Condition.” International Conference on  Subjectivity/Cultural Identity in An Age of Globalization. Taipei:  Shih-Shin University  (co-hosted by University of Alberta,   Canada). 

                  2001. 11.  “Beyond Boundaries: Breaking Through  Postcolonial Cultural Identities.” International Conference on  Transforming Cultures/Shifting Boundaries. Australia:  The University of   Queensland.

                  2001. 12.  “Women in Fear: A Feminist Dystopia in The  Handmaid’s Tale.” Seminar on Language and Literature. Tainan: National   Cheng Kung   University.

                  2002. 04.  “Diasporic Desire: Deterritorializing  Identity inGish Jen’s Mona in the Promised Land.” ACLA 2002  Annual Conference. Puerto Rico: American Comparative Literature Association  (co-hosted by the University   of Puerto Rico).

                  2002. 12.  “Encountering the Cultural Aporia:  Multiculturalism as a Global/Local Cultural Nexus.” 5th  International Convention Forum on Contemporary Theory. India: Maharaja Sayajirao University of  Shillong, India (co-hosted by Louisiana    State University, U.S.A.).

                  2003. 03.  “Altered Narrative: A Narratee-Oriented  Narrative in Midnight Children.” Conference on Language and  Literature. Tainan: National Cheng   Kung University.

